programme.desc: A letter incriminates a widow, whose dead husband wrote it when he suspected her of plotting to kill him. (Repeat).

programme.title: High Wall
programme.desc: A World War II veteran suffering from a recurring brain injury teams with a woman psychiatrist to prove himself innocent of his wife's murder. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Wrong Man
programme.desc: A different kind of Alfred Hitchcock film: a fact-based, semi-documentary account of a New York City musician who is falsely accused of an armed robbery and the nightmarish impact it has on him and his family, especially his mentally unstable wife. The idea for the motion picture came when Hitchcock read about the miscarriage of justice in a Life magazine article. (Repeat).

programme.title: Murder Is My Beat
programme.desc: A detective (Paul Langton) arrests a singer (Barbara Payton) for murder but begins to believe she is innocent. Mrs. Abbott: Selena Royle. Hawley: Robert Shayne. Abbott: Roy Gordon. Edgar G. Ulmer directed. (Repeat).

programme.title: Moontide

Woman on Boat: Helene Reynolds. Effective script by John O'Hara, from the novel by Willard Robertson. Realistic. Archie Mayo, Fritz Lang directed. (Repeat).

programme.title: Tokyo Joe
programme.desc: Humphrey Bogart as an ex-serviceman and war hero in postwar Tokyo, where he gets blackmailed by a Japanese royal into participating in a plot to smuggle war criminals back into the country. (Repeat).

programme.title: Sirocco
programme.desc: A Damascus casino operator runs afoul of his allies when he runs guns to the insurrectionists who are attempting to overthrow the local French protectorate. (Repeat).

programme.title: They Live by Night
programme.desc: Two young criminal lovebirds try to escape from their past and the law, but find it tough to evade both. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Lady in the Lake
programme.desc: Subjective camera work allows the viewer to see this film-noir mystery transpire through the eyes of a private detective who finds murder while investigating the case of a missing woman. The script was adapted from the Raymond Chandler novel; and Robert Montgomery directed and stars as private eye Philip Marlowe. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Daisy Kenyon
programme.desc: Tidy triangle: career woman (Joan Crawford), married man (Dana Andrews) and ex-GI (Henry Fonda). Smooth Otto Preminger direction. Lucile: Ruth Warrick. Mary: Martha Stewart. Marie: Connie Marshall. Rosamund: Peggy Ann Garner. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Island in the Sky
programme.desc: The secretary (Gloria Stuart) to an assistant DA (Michael Whalen) tries to prove a man innocent. Doyle: Paul Kelly. Peter: Robert Kellard. Lucy: June Storey. Marty: Leon Ames. (Repeat).(n)

programme.desc: An English writer named Basil arrives on the isle of Crete in the hopes of realigning his values and outlook on life. He is "adopted" by the flamboyant Zorba, who decides to educate Basil in the ways of the world.
